-> lsmod
    ( list of loaded kernel modules )

-> modprobe
    ( util for manage modules )
    -> modprobe -l
        ( all available kernel modules)

    -> modprobe { module name }
        ( download kernel module )

    -> modprobe -r { module name }
        ( unload kernel module )

    -> modinfo { module name }
        ( module info )

    -> path to kernel module example:
        -> /lib/modules/$(uname -r)
        -> modules for set them in system load:
            -> /etc/modules